%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EGrace%20Sun%2C%20a%2016-year-old%20from%20Kentucky%2C%20won%20%2475%2C000%20for%20her%20research%20on%20biomedical%20devices.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20took%20home%20the%20top%20prize%20at%20the%20ISEF%20%E2%80%94%20the%20%26quot%3Bgranddaddy%20of%20all%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Farchimedes-death-ray-science-fair-project-middle-school-teen-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Escience%20fairs%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHer%20work%20on%20organic%20electronic%20devices%20aims%20to%20make%20medical%20implants%20safer%20and%20more%20effective.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EGrace%20Sun%20can't%20drive%20yet.%20Unlike%20many%2016-year-olds%2C%20getting%20her%20license%20hasn't%20been%20her%20top%20priority.%20Instead%2C%20she's%20been%20busy%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fregeneron-science-talent-search-winner-achyuta-rajaram-machine-learning-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eworking%20on%20a%20project%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20revolutionize%20biomedicine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20high%20schooler%20from%20Lexington%2C%20Kentucky%2C%20developed%20a%20new%20technique%20to%20improve%20organic%20electronic%20devices.%20The%20technology%20could%20someday%20make%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsynchron-brain-computer-chip-implant-elon-musk-neuralink-human-trial-2021-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emedical%20implants%3C%2Fa%3E%20significantly%20more%20compatible%20with%20human%20bodies%20and%20far%20less%20invasive.%20It%20could%20also%20lead%20to%20new%20early-diagnosis%20tools%20for%20a%20wide%20variety%20of%20diseases.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Friday%20she%20won%20%2475%2C000%20for%20her%20research.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20called%20my%20name.%20I%20thought%20they%20got%20the%20wrong%20person.%20I%20was%20like%2C%20is%20there%20another%20Grace%20up%20here%3F%26quot%3B%20Sun%20told%20Business%20Insider%20backstage%20at%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fregeneron-international-science-fair-high-school-students-school-shootings-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERegeneron%20International%20Science%20and%20Engineering%20Fair%3C%2Fa%3E%20(ISEF)%20awards%20ceremony.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20hands%20were%20trembling%20and%20a%20huge%20smile%20beamed%20across%20her%20face.%20Just%20minutes%20before%2C%20rainbow%20confetti%20had%20exploded%20behind%20her%20on%20stage%20in%20front%20of%20hundreds%20of%20her%20peers%2C%20while%20lights%20flashed%20and%20peppy%20music%20boomed%20over%20the%20audience.%20She%20suddenly%20held%20a%20trophy%20in%20her%20hands.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20in%20disbelief%20because%20of%20how%20good%20everyone%20else%20is%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20exhilaration%2C%20though%2C%20Sun%20easily%20slipped%20into%20a%20calm%20and%20authoritative%20demeanor%20to%20explain%20her%20research%2C%20which%20focused%20on%20organic%20electrochemical%20transistors%2C%20or%20OECTs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20have%20performance%20issues%20right%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%20of%20the%20devices.%20%26quot%3BThey%20have%20instability%20in%20the%20body.%20You%20don't%20want%20some%20sort%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-bill-gates-jeff-bezos-invest-in-brain-implants-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eimplanted%20bioelectronic%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20degrade%20in%20your%20body.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20OECTs%20have%20huge%20potential.%20Compared%20to%20other%20devices%20made%20of%20silicon%2C%20they're%20soft%20and%20flexible.%20That%20makes%20them%20a%20better%20fit%20for%20heart%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finterest-neuralink-human-trial-patient-elon-musk-brain-implant-report-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebrain%20implants%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey're%20so%20much%20more%20accurate%2C%20their%20speed%20is%20higher%2C%20their%20performance%20is%20higher%20because%20they%20consider%20signals%20in%20the%20body%20that%20previous%20electronics%20haven't%20considered.%20They're%20also%20safe%20because%20they're%20made%20of%20organic%20materials%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20hopes%20that%20her%20work%20improving%20their%20performance%20can%20be%20a%20first%20step%20to%20commercializing%20them%20and%20getting%20them%20into%20wide%20use%2C%20within%20the%20next%20two%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2266aca2be-a3b5-4d69-b1ad-6c96b243b249%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ESun%20won%20the%20Olympics%20of%20science%20fairs%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EISEF%20is%20the%20world's%20biggest%20pre-college%20STEM%20competition%2C%20run%20by%20the%20Society%20for%20Science.%20It's%20like%20the%20Olympics%20of%20science%20or%20the%20%26quot%3Bgrandaddy%20of%20all%20science%20fairs%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20judging%20chair%20Christopher%20Gould.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENearly%202%2C000%20students%20spent%20the%20week%20in%20Los%20Angeles%20attending%20talks%2C%20mingling%2C%20and%20defending%20their%20research%20to%20judges.%20The%20event%20doled%20out%20%249%20million%20in%20awards%20this%20year%20%E2%80%94%20its%20largest%20purse%20yet.%20But%20Sun%20took%20home%20the%20biggest%20sum%20with%20the%20%2475%2C000%20George%20D.%20Yancopoulos%20Innovator%20Award.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20was%20our%20number%20one%20project%2C%20without%20a%20shadow%20of%20a%20doubt%2C%26quot%3B%20Ian%20Jandrell%2C%20a%20judging%20co-chair%20for%20the%20materials%20science%20category%20at%20ISEF%2C%20told%20BI%20about%20Sun's%20research.%20He%20oversaw%20hours%20of%20discussion%20among%20the%20materials-science%20judges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20crystal%20clear%20that%20that%20room%20was%20convinced%20that%20this%20was%20a%20significant%20project%20and%20worthy%20of%20consideration%20for%20a%20very%20top%20award%20because%20of%20the%20contribution%20that%20was%20made%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearch%20at%20ISEF%20is%20not%20peer-reviewed%2C%20so%20it's%20not%20held%20to%20the%20standard%20that%20studies%20published%20in%20journals%20like%20Nature%20or%20JAMA%20must%20meet.%20Instead%2C%20ISEF%20encourages%20students%20to%20learn%20about%20the%20scientific%20process%20by%20doing%20it%20themselves%20and%20defending%20their%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJandrell%20said%20the%20judges%20were%20impressed%20by%20%26quot%3Bthe%20sophistication%20and%20the%20diligence%26quot%3B%20of%20Sun's%20research%20and%20her%20ability%20to%20explain%20it%20and%20respond%20to%20questions%20on%20the%20spot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20the%20whole%20package%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e2f03e1b-5c68-4381-b823-a95ce87d277f%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ELong%20days%20in%20a%20university%20lab%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222250%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20girl%20in%20blue%20shirt%20with%20long%20dark%20hair%20holds%20a%20small%20OETC%20device%20that%20looks%20like%20a%20small%20clear%20square%20with%20white%20inside%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6647c9cc9fc063e829b2978d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGrace%20Sun%20holds%20an%20OECT%20device%20that%20helped%20her%20win%20the%20ISEF%20science%20fair.%3Cp%3EChris%20Ayers%2FSociety%20for%20Science%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESun%20has%20been%20working%20on%20her%20project%20for%20over%20six%20months.%20It%20took%20long%20hours%2C%20and%20much%20of%20it%20needed%20to%20be%20done%20in%20a%20lab%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Kentucky.%20The%20devices%20she%20worked%20on%20were%20tiny%2C%20small%20enough%20to%20fit%20on%20your%20thumb.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20a%20few%20weeks%2C%20she%20left%20school%20three%20hours%20early%20to%20work%20in%20a%20lab%20for%20another%20five%20hours.%20Luckily%2C%20her%20teachers%20were%20understanding%20about%20why%20she%20needed%20extensions%20on%20some%20of%20her%20assignments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESun%20engineered%20a%20new%20technique%20to%20improve%20the%20devices'%20performance%20and%20take%20them%20closer%20to%20commercial%20use.%20In%20the%20research%20that%20snagged%20the%20five-figure%20award%2C%20Sun%20tried%20%26quot%3Bdoping%26quot%3B%20the%20OECTs%20%E2%80%94%20introducing%20chemical%20impurities%20to%20see%20how%20they%20affected%20the%20device's%20electrical%20properties%20%E2%80%94%20with%20a%20series%20of%20organic%20salts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20found%20that%20one%20salt%2C%20called%20tetrabutylammonium%20chloride%2C%20was%20especially%20effective%20because%20it%20improved%20the%20device's%20amplification%20abilities%2C%20sensitivity%2C%20signal-to-noise%20ratio%2C%20and%20switching%20speed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20qualities%20are%20important%20because%20they%20improve%20overall%20performance%2C%20which%20could%20one%20day%20help%20create%20biomedical%20devices%20capable%20of%20detecting%20early%20hints%20of%20disease%20in%20your%20body's%20biochemical%20makeup.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20salt%20that%20Sun%20tested%20improved%20amplification%20performance%20by%2097%25%20and%20switching%20speed%20by%2077%25%2C%20Sun%20found.%20%26quot%3BThese%20are%20significant%20numbers%2C%26quot%3B%20Jandrell%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESensitive%20OECTs%20could%20detect%20proteins%20or%20nucleic%20acids%20that%20correspond%20with%20the%20disease%20long%20before%20traditional%20symptoms%20appear.%20Sun%20imagines%20OECTs%20embedded%20in%20clothing%20to%20monitor%20swea%20or%20used%20to%20accurately%20test%20blood-alcohol%20levels%20before%20you%20drive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEventually%2C%20OECTs%20could%20lead%20to%20new%20technologies%20that%20replace%20invasive%20implants%20like%20pacemakers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20Sun%2C%20she%20sees%20a%20future%20for%20herself%20in%20chemical%20engineering%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-chatbots-tech-doctors-medicine-healthcare-system-empathy-quality-email-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehelp%20improve%20medicine%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHopefully%20I%20can%20make%20some%20sort%20of%20commercializable%20breakthrough%2C%20like%20what%20I'm%20trying%20to%20do%20now%20with%20these%20devices%2C%26quot%3B%20Sun%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20possible%2C%20I%20do%20want%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhealthcare-biotech-pitch-decks-that-raised-millions-from-vc-investors%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estart%20a%20business%3C%2Fa%3E%20so%20that%20I%20can%20get%20them%20into%20the%20real%20world%20in%20industries%20to%20impact%20more%20people%20directly.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fteen-wins-isef-science-fair-grand-prize-discovery-biomedical-devices-2024-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1715987685000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6647cf309fc063e829b29961%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fteen-wins-isef-science-fair-grand-prize-discovery-biomedical-devices-2024-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Grace%20Sun%20won%20the%20ISEF%20science%20fair%20for%20her%20work%20on%20OECTs%2C%20which%20have%20benefits%20over%20current%20biomedical%20devices%20and%20could%20help%20a%20variety%20of%20diseases.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22mmcfalljohnsen%40businessinsider.com%20(Morgan%20McFall-Johnsen%2CJenny%20McGrath)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A29%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fteen-wins-isef-science-fair-grand-prize-discovery-biomedical-devices-2024-5%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ceramist%20Katie%20Kimmel%20Talks%20New%20Row%20DTLA%20Pop-Up%2C%20Her%20Talk%20Show%20Father%E2%80%99s%20Artistic%20Talents%20and%20the%20One%20Commis