3Cli%3EI%20want%20to%20retire%20a%20millionaire%2C%20so%20I%20asked%20a%20financial%20planner%20to%20look%20at%20my%20strategy%20so%20far.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EHe%20said%20I%20need%20more%20tax%20diversification%20and%20income%20streams%2C%20and%20a%20plan%20for%20retirement%20income.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EHe%20told%20me%20I%20need%20to%20contribute%20to%20my%20retirement%20account%20more%20often%2C%20not%20randomly%20throughout%20the%20year.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20past%20two%20years%2C%20I've%20been%20working%20hard%20to%20reach%20my%20goal%20of%20retiring%20as%20a%20millionaire.%20I%20knew%20this%20would%20be%20a%20challenge%2C%20since%20I%20only%20started%20saving%20for%20retirement%20in%20my%20early%2030s%2C%20but%20I%20still%20decided%20it%20was%20something%20I%20wanted%20to%20achieve%20so%20I%20could%20spend%20my%20later%20years%20living%20comfortably.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20I%20took%20some%20steps%20to%20start%20putting%20this%20plan%20into%20motion%2C%20like%20opening%20a%20SEP%20IRA%20and%20adjusting%20my%20spending%20habits%2C%20I%20knew%20I%20had%20a%20lot%20more%20work%20to%20do.%20That's%20why%20I%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fhow-to-find-financial-advisor%5C%22%3Efound%20a%20financial%20advisor%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20I%20asked%20financial%20planner%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.greenbeatfinancial.com%2Fabout%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAdam%20Scherer%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20review%20my%20retirement%20portfolio%20and%20tell%20me%20if%20I'm%20on%20track%20to%20retire%20as%20a%20millionaire.%20He%20said%20I'm%20making%20four%20mistakes%20that%20are%20holding%20me%20back%20from%20reaching%20my%20future%20goal.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20I%20only%20contribute%20to%20my%20SEP%20IRA%20a%20few%20times%20a%20year%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEver%20since%20opening%20up%20my%20first%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-retirement-plans%5C%22%3Eretirement%20plan%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20age%20of%2030%2C%20I%20vowed%20to%20make%20frequent%20contributions%20to%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fsep-ira%5C%22%3ESEP%20IRA%3C%2Fa%3E.%20At%20first%2C%20I%20was%20good%20about%20depositing%20money%20monthly.%20But%20as%20time%20went%20on%2C%20I%20found%20myself%20forgetting%20to%20do%20this%20or%20just%20tempted%20to%20use%20that%20cash%20on%20purchases%20instead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScherer%20says%20one%20main%20downside%20to%20not%20contributing%20monthly%20is%20that%20I'm%20missing%20out%20on%20opportunities%20to%20buy%20into%20investments%20when%20they%20are%20potentially%20priced%20lower%20due%20to%20normal%20market%20or%20economic%20fluctuations.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20way%20to%20fix%20this%20mistake%20is%20to%20automate%20my%20contributions.%20Scherer%20says%20that%20setting%20up%20a%20monthly%20automatic%20transfer%20to%20my%20SEP%20IRA%20will%20put%20less%20pressure%20on%20my%20overall%20cash%20flow%20and%20help%20me%20develop%20a%20positive%20retirement%20savings%20habit%20that%20could%20pay%20off%20in%20the%20long%20run.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20I%20don't%20have%20any%20tax%20diversification%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20opened%20up%20my%20SEP%20IRA%20a%20few%20years%20ago%2C%20I%20thought%20that%20was%20the%20only%20account%20I%20needed%20to%20help%20me%20plan%20for%20retirement.%20It%20turns%20out%20I%20was%20wrong.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScherer%20says%20that%20tax%20diversification%2C%20the%20strategy%20of%20having%20assets%20in%20accounts%20with%20varying%20tax%20treatments%20(such%20as%20tax-deferred%2C%20taxable%2C%20and%20tax-free%20accounts)%2C%20allows%20for%20a%20smoother%20retirement%20income%20strategy%20and%20generates%20tax%20savings.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20your%20invested%20assets%20are%20located%20in%20a%20single%20account%20type%2C%20the%20options%20available%20to%20meet%20your%20retirement%20income%20needs%20in%20a%20tax-efficient%20manner%20become%20more%20limited%20and%20could%20result%20in%20additional%20taxation%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Scherer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20help%20my%20retirement%20savings%20grow%2C%20Scherer%20recommends%20establishing%20accounts%20with%20varying%20tax%20treatments.%20For%20example%2C%20as%20a%20self-employed%20individual%2C%20I%20can%20have%20my%20SEP%20IRA%20as%20a%20tax-deferred%20account%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-online-brokerage%5C%22%3Ebrokerage%20account%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20is%20taxable%2C%20and%20a%20Roth%20IRA%2C%20which%20offers%20tax-free%20withdrawals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOver%20time%2C%20adjust%20the%20location%20of%20your%20contributions%20so%20the%20result%20is%20a%20balanced%2C%20tax-diversified%20allocation%20as%20you%20head%20into%20retirement%3A%2033%25%20in%20taxable%20accounts%2C%2033%25%20in%20tax-free%20accounts%2C%2034%25%20in%20tax-deferred%20accounts%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Scherer.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20I%20don't%20have%20a%20retirement%20income%20strategy%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20I%20want%20to%20retire%20as%20a%20millionaire%2C%20I%20don't%20have%20a%20viable%20plan%20in%20place%20to%20help%20me%20achieve%20that%20goal.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScherer%20points%20out%20that%20if%20I%20want%20to%20reach%20this%20goal%2C%20I%20need%20to%20account%20for%20variables%20like%20my%20earnings%2C%20the%20length%20of%20time%20until%20retirement%2C%20the%20length%20of%20time%20I'll%20be%20in%20retirement%2C%20the%20effect%20of%20inflation%20on%20the%20value%20of%20my%20savings%2C%20an%20estimate%20of%20my%20living%20expenses%20throughout%20retirement%2C%20additional%20savings%20for%20contingencies%20(traveling%2C%20health-related%20issues%2C%20gifting)%2C%20and%20a%20required%20rate%20of%20return%20on%20my%20invested%20assets%20to%20get%20me%20to%20my%20goal%20in%20the%20timeframe%20I%20desire.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20begin%20figuring%20out%20this%20strategy%2C%20Scherer%20recommends%20using%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fretirement-calculator%5C%22%3Eretirement%20calculator%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20working%20closely%20with%20a%20financial%20planner.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20I%20don't%20have%20enough%20income%20streams%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAside%20from%20my%20businesses%20and%20side%20hustles%2C%20I%20don't%20have%20many%20other%20fluid%20streams%20of%20income.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYour%20current%20earnings%20provide%20you%20with%20the%20opportunity%20to%20spend%20on%20things%20that%20you%20value%20today%20and%20save%20for%20your%20future%20self%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Scherer.%20%26quot%3BBy%20having%20more%20sources%20of%20income%2C%20whether%20active%20(earnings)%2C%20passive%2C%20or%20portfolio%2C%20a%20balance%20of%20saving%20and%20spending%20that%20truly%20aligns%20with%20your%20values%20and%20dreams%20becomes%20easier.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScherer%20says%20one%20way%20to%20develop%20a%20passive%20income%20stream%20is%20to%20allocate%20investments%20to%20income-generating%20vehicles%2C%20such%20as%20dividend-paying%20stocks%20or%20coupon-bearing%20bonds.%20He%20also%20recommends%20looking%20into%20rental%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-real-estate-investing-platforms%5C%22%3Ereal%20estate%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20investing%20as%20a%20silent%20partner%20in%20other%20businesses%20as%20another%20passive%20income%20generator.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUltimately%2C%20any%20of%20these%20alternatives%20need%20to%20be%20reviewed%20and%20selected%20only%20if%20they%20align%20with%20your%20overall%20retirement%20strategy%20and%20personal%20values%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Scherer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsmartasset