6quot%3B%20Mr%20Jaishankar%20said%2C%20responding%20to%20a%20question.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20not%20completely%20and%20utterly%20prohibited%20people%20working%20with%20China%20but%20frankly%2C%20we%20would%20much%20rather%20you%20work%20with%20Indian%20companies%20if%20there%20is%20an%20Indian%20option%20available%20to%20you.%20That%20I%20think%20is%20good%20for%20our%20national%20security%2C%20we%20hope%20you%20think%20that%20it%20is%20good%20for%20your%20own%20business%20in%20the%20long%20term%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20external%20affairs%20minister%20underlined%20the%20need%20for%20using%20a%20%26quot%3Bnational%20security%20filter%26quot%3B%20in%20doing%20business%20with%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20a%20specific%20query%20on%20the%20border%20row%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BWould%20you%20do%20business%20with%20somebody%20who%20has%20just%20barged%20into%20your%20drawing%20room%20and%20is%20trying%20to%20make%20a%20mess%20of%20your%20house%20fencing%3F%20You%20won't.%20There%20is%20a%20common%20sense%20proposition%20there.%26quot%3B%20In%20remarks%20seen%20as%20a%20reference%20to%20China%2C%20Mr%20Jaishankar%2C%20in%20his%20address%2C%20flagged%20concerns%20over%20the%20%26quot%3Bweaponisation%26quot%3B%20of%20economic%20activity%20and%20how%20access%20to%20raw%20materials%20or%20even%20stability%20of%20tourism%20are%20being%20utilised%20to%20exert%20political%20pressure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20different%20dimension%20of%20the%20concerns%20that%20we%20harbour%20is%20one%20emanating%20from%20a%20combination%20of%20excessive%20market%20shares%2C%20financial%20domination%20and%20technology%20tracking%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBetween%20them%2C%20they%20have%20actually%20allowed%20for%20the%20weaponisation%20of%20virtually%20any%20form%20of%20economic%20activity.%20We%20have%20seen%20how%20both%20exports%20and%20imports%2C%20access%20to%20raw%20materials%20or%20even%20stability%20of%20tourism%20has%20been%20utilised%20to%20exert%20political%20pressure%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Jaishankar%20said%20the%20current%20times%20call%20for%20something%20more%20than%20business%20as%20usual.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBecause%20trust%20and%20reliability%20have%20become%20so%20important%2C%20foreign%20policy%20is%20today%20charged%20with%20creating%20the%20comfort%20levels%20between%20governments%20to%20make%20that%20happen%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20especially%20so%20in%20terms%20of%20de-risking%20supply%20sources%20and%20enhancing%20collaboration%20in%20sensitive%2C%20critical%20and%20emerging%20technologies%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20can%20already%20see%20that%20unfold%20with%20the%20US%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20iCET%20dialogue%20that%20we%20had%20and%20with%20the%20EU%20in%20the%20Trade%20and%20Technology%20Council%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Jaishankar%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20there%20is%20a%20need%20to%20recognise%20that%20India's%20economic%20priorities%20will%20have%20to%20align%20with%20its%20strategic%20interests.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAn%20economy%20with%20India's%20prospects%20also%20has%20to%20look%20at%20accessing%20global%20resources%20more%20seriously%20if%20we%20are%20to%20fuel%20our%20growth%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20minister%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20long%2C%20we%20have%20looked%20at%20Russia%20from%20a%20political%20or%20security%20perspective.%20As%20that%20country%20turns%20eastwards%2C%20fresh%20economic%20opportunities%20are%20presenting%20themselves%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20spike%20in%20our%20trade%20and%20the%20new%20areas%20of%20cooperation%20should%20not%20be%20regarded%20as%20a%20temporary%20phenomenon%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Jaishankar%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20s