he%20threshold%20for%20a%20heat%20wave%20is%20met%20when%20the%20maximum%20temperature%20of%20a%20weather%20station%20reaches%20at%20least%2040%20degrees%20Celsius%20in%20the%20plains%2C%2037%20degrees%20in%20the%20coastal%20areas%2C%20and%2030%20degrees%20in%20the%20hilly%20regions%2C%20and%20the%20departure%20from%20normal%20is%20at%20least%204.5%20notches.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20severe%20heat%20wave%20is%20declared%20if%20the%20departure%20from%20normal%20exceeds%206.4%20notches.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Friday%2C%20the%20maximum%20temperature%20surged%20to%2047.4%20degrees%20Celsius%20in%20Najafgarh%20and%2047.1%20in%20Haryana's%20Sirsa.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20India%20Meteorological%20Data%20(IMD)%20data%20till%207%3A30%20pm%2C%20Najafgarh%20was%20the%20warmest%20place%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Delhi%2C%20the%20mercury%20settled%20at%2046.5%20degrees%20Celsius%20in%20Mungeshpur%2C%2046.2%20degrees%20in%20Aya%20Nagar%2C%2045.9%20degrees%20in%20Pusa%20and%20Jafarpur%2C%2045.8%20degrees%20in%20Pitampura%20and%2045.1%20degrees%20in%20Palam.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESevere%20heatwave%20conditions%20are%20very%20likely%20in%20some%20parts%20of%20Rajasthan%2C%20Punjab%2C%20Haryana%20and%20Delhi%20during%20May%2018-21%2C%20the%20IMD%20warned.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20fresh%20heatwave%20spell%20will%20commence%20over%20east%20and%20central%20India%20from%20Saturday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Met%20office%20issued%20a%20red%20alert%20for%20west%20Rajasthan%2C%20stressing%20the%20need%20for%20%26quot%3Bextreme%20care%20for%20vulnerable%20people%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20issued%20an%20orange%20alert%20for%20Haryana%2C%20Punjab%2C%20east%20Rajasthan%2C%20Delhi%2C%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20Bihar%20and%20Gujarat%20and%20emphasised%20%26quot%3Bhigh%20health%20concern%26quot%3B%20for%20vulnerable%20people%2C%20including%20infants%2C%20the%20elderly%20and%20those%20with%20chronic%20diseases.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20warned%20of%20an%20increased%20likelihood%20of%20heat-related%20illnesses%20in%20people%20exposed%20to%20the%20sun%20for%20prolonged%20periods%20or%20engaging%20in%20heavy%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Met%20office%20had%20earlier%20predicted%20a%20higher-than-normal%20number%20of%20heatwave%20days%20in%20the%20northern%20plains%20and%20central%20India%20in%20May.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENormally%2C%20the%20northern%20plains%2C%20central%20India%20and%20adjoining%20areas%20of%20peninsular%20India%20experience%20around%20three%20heatwave%20days%20in%20May.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EApril%20witnessed%20record-smashing%20maximum%20temperatures%20in%20east%2C%20northeast%2C%20and%20southern%20peninsular%20India%2C%20prompting%20health%20warnings%20from%20government%20agencies%20and%20a%20few%20states%20to%20suspend%20in-person%20classes%20in%20schools.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeveral%20places%20recorded%20their%20highest-ever%20April%20day%20temperatures%2C%20with%20the%20mercury%20soaring%20to%2047%20degrees%20Celsius.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20least%20two%20people%20died%20in%20Kerala%20due%20to%20suspected%20heatstroke%20during%20this%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20IMD%20data%2C%20heatwave%20days%20in%20April%20were%20the%20highest%20in%2015%20years%20in%20Gangetic%20West%20Bengal%20and%20nine%20years%20in%20Odisha.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%2016%20days%2C%20Odisha%20also%20experienced%20the%20longest%20heatwave%20spell%20in%20April%20since%202016.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Wednesday%2C%20a%20group%20of%20leading%20climate%20scientists%20said%20similar%20heat%20waves%20could%20occur%20once%20every%2030%20years%2C%20and%20these%20have%20already%20become%20about%2045%20times%20more%20likely%20due%20to%20climate%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20scientists%20from%20the%20World%20Weather%20Attribution%20group%20emphasised%20that%20heat%20waves%20intensified%20by%20climate%20change%20are%20making%20life%20much%20tougher%20for%20people%20living%20in%20poverty%20across%20Asia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E